# Each person should make his or her own [[decision]]s.
#: ''You can get there by bus, or train, or taxi. Whatever. '''You pays your money and you takes your choice'''.''
#* {{quote-journal|journal=Punch|page=17|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tJNEAAAAcAAJ|year=1846|title=THE MINISTERIAL CRISIS.[cartoon]|passage=Showman. On your right you will perceive a Prime Minister a Bolishing of hisself. And over your left is another Prime Minister a Bolishing of the Corn-Laws.&nbsp;/ Master John Bull. But which is the Prime Minister?&nbsp;/ Showman. Which ever you please, my little dear. '''You pays your money, and you takes your choice.'''|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=tJNEAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA17&dq=%22you+pays+your+money+and+you+takes+your+choice%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=oOH1VLO8M4-p7AaesIAY&ved=0CGMQ6AEwDA#v=onepage&q=%22you%20pays%20your%20money%20and%20you%20takes%20your%20choice%22&f=false}}

====Usage notes====
* This phrase is almost always expressed in the ungrammatical form: ''you '''pays''''' and ''you '''takes'''''.

